Adam Johnson has been suspended by Sunderland after his arrest on suspicion of sexual activity with a girl under the age of 16 and will miss Tuesday night's Premier League game at Hull City.

Although he has not played for England for almost three years, Johnson has established himself as a Premier League winger having operated at Middlesbrough, Manchester City and Sunderland.

Johnson has also commanded almost £20million in transfer fees during his career. Here,Sportsmail takes a look at his timeline.

